"***Question 1: \"How likely is it that Bond will escape from Le Chiffre?\"***\n1. Not very likely\n\nBond has just been caught off guard by Le Chiffre and his gunmen, and he has been disarmed. He was able to fend off one of the gunmen initially, but he was quickly overpowered. He is now being searched and handled roughly by Le Chiffre's men. These circumstances suggest that his chances of escape are low.\n\n***Question 2: \"How suspenseful do you find this passage to be?\"***\n7. Extremely suspenseful\n\nThe passage is suspenseful because it sets up a tense and unexpected situation. Bond, who had been confident and in control, is suddenly caught off guard and overpowered. The reader is left wondering how Bond will escape from this predicament, and the use of phrases like \"Bond felt puny and impotent\" adds to the sense of tension and unease.\n\nQuestion 1: 1."